article.headline: Drake 77, Evansville 68
article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. (AP) -- Lucious Wagner had 19 points and six assists to lead Evansville to a 77-68 win over Drake on Saturday night. Bradley Strickland added 16 points and Clint Cuffle scored 11 for the Purple Aces (4-16, 3-9 Missouri Valley), who shot 49 percent from the field. Nick Grant scored 14 points on 5-of-8 shooting to lead Drake (9-11, 5-7). Drake led 35-32 at halftime. Quantel Murphy's jumper gave the Bulldogs a 43-42 edge with just over 15 minutes to play, but that was the last time Drake held the lead. Evansville outscored Drake 22-12 over a seven minute stretch late in the second half. Wagner scored nine points, including two of his three 3-pointers, during the run to help Evansville take control. Strickland's tip-in gave the Purple Aces their biggest lead of the game, 75-61, with 1:40 to play. Chaun Brooks scored 12 points and Klayton Korver added 11 points and five rebounds for Drake.
